OpenBSD router notes
Raspbery Pi 4 1gb

OpenBSD 7.5

miniroot75.img

Install on Raspberry Pi:

watch for the OpenBSD BOOTAA64 "boot>" prompt,
  and type "set tty fb0".

ls to see files

boot [file] to boot into a file.


hostname - fire


